rview Availability Reviews (369) Photos (75) Favorite Favorite Favorite Review What is Permafrost? Permafrost, bred\u00a0by Rogue Buds,\u00a0is a sativa-dominant hybrid named for its frosty coat of crystal trichomes and fresh pine aroma. While some believe Permafrost to be the love child of Trainwreck and White Widow, others claim it comes from Kali Mist and Trinity Snow. True to its hybrid genetics, Permafrost\u2019s relaxing effects are balanced between mind and body. Larger doses demonstrate the strain\u2019s potency:\u00a0as sensory detail peaks, attention becomes transfixed, and a full-body calm takes over. For this reason, Permafrost may help patients treating ADD/ADHD and anxiety symptoms, and others have reported its success in treating arthritis, asthma, multiple sclerosis, and gastrointestinal disorders. Where to Buy Permafrost View All () Permafrost Effects and Attributes Effects Medical Negatives Euphoric Energetic Uplifted Happy Relaxed Depression Stress Pain Fatigue Headaches Dry Mouth Dry Eyes Anxious Dizzy Paranoid Permafrost Genetics and Grow Info Lineage Parents of Permafrost Trainwreck {{value}} {{symbol}}Tw {{category}}Hybrid White Widow {{value}} {{symbol}}Ww {{category}}Hybrid Permafrost Flavors 1. Earthy 2. Pine 3. Sweet Review Highlights View All (369) Most Helpful lorian 11/5/2014 10:59 PM 11/5/2014 10:59 PM \u201cI still like this stain better than most. Tastes good, you get nice and high and it doesn't give you couch lock , so you can get your stuff done during the day.\u201d Read Full Review Report Abuse Most Recent ariel. 2/1/2019 8:06 PM 2/1/2019 8:06 PM \u201ctook a hit so hard i fell over and dropped my bong. this is the greatest strain i have ever smoked.\u201d Read Full Review Report Abuse Photos View All (75) Most Popular In Seattle, WA Spokane, WA Puyallup, WA Tacoma, WA Bellingham, WA Bremerton, WA Everett, WA Lynnwood, WA Mount Vernon, WA Portland, OR Articles View All The 6 Best Documentaries to Watch While High Celebrate Chine