arbon in yet frozen ground. Here the authors show that the consequence of these changes is global warming of permafrost at depths greater than 10 m in the Northern Hemisphere, in mountains, and in Ant...International Permafrost AssociationJanuary 16 \u00b7 It's just the start of 2019, but it is already time to start thinking about the 12th International Conference on Permafrost happening in June 2020! Check out the website developed by the Local Organizing Committee and propose sessions by the end of the month.icop2020.csp.escience.cnThe 12th International Conference on Permafrost: HomeThe 12th InternationalConference on Permafrost (ICOP 2020) will be held in Lanzhou, China, from June 22-26, 2020. The conference themeis \"Permafrost environments under persistent warming: Challenges for scientific assessment and engineering practice\".On behalf of the local organizing committee, I wa...International Permafrost AssociationNovember 20, 2018 \u00b7 Call for permafrost enthusiasts: fill out this very brief survey on inspirational permafrost resources for a project organized by Ylva Sj\u00f6berg, Ashley Rudy, Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Bouchard, Julie Malenfant-Lepage, Marc Oliva, Matthias Siewert, Michael Fritz, and Michel Paquette.docs.google.comPermafrost Science: Sources of InspirationWe all get our ideas from somewhere. We are generally inspired by the works of other scientists in our own field, or sometimes in completely different fields of science. We are conducting a review initiative about the most influential papers or books (or other documents) in permafrost research, from...International Permafrost AssociationNovember 15, 2018 \u00b7 Looking for a permafrost job? Consider this Geotechnical Data Scientist position in Yellowknife! Applications close November 23.gov.nt.caGeotechnical Data ScientistThe Department of Industry, Tourism and Investment (ITI) works through wide-ranging partnerships and initiatives to deliver quality programs and services that promote and suppo