ociationSeptember 26, 2018 \u00b7 Registration is currently open for the inaugural annual meeting of the Canadian Permafrost Association (CPA)! The IPA encourages those working with permafrost in Canada to consider attending this meeting at Yukon College in Whitehorse. We are pleased to see this growing national network. \ud83c\udde8\ud83c\udde6\ufe0fyukoncollege.yk.caCanadian Permafrost Association Annual General Meeting | Yukon CollegeRegister now! October 10-12th, 2018 Yukon College, Whitehorse, Yukon We are pleased to announce the inaugural annual general meeting for the Canadian Permafrost Association (CPA). The CPA is being formed to address the multidisciplinary nature of permafrost - bridging natural and social sciences, en...International Permafrost Association added 5 new photos.July 3, 2018 \u00b7 This past weekend approximately 30 EUCOP5 participants joined local experts for regional excursions in three locations: Aosta Valley (Italy), the Valais Alps (Switzerland), and the \u00c9crins massif (France). The Valais Alps excursion, led by Christophe Lambiel of University of Lausanne and Reynald Delaloye of University of Fribourg, focused on alpine permafrost and its connection with geohazards. On the first day, the group visited Mont-Fort (3328 masl) and discussed glaciation and permafrost temperatures in this area. On the second day, participants were able to walk on top of fast-moving rock glaciers and learn about how these landforms impact the villages below by causing rockfall and debris flows.+2International Permafrost Association added 5 new photos.June 29, 2018 \u00b7 EUCOP5 officially closed on Thursday, though activities have continued with local excursions on Friday and regional excursions going over the weekend. The conference was a fantastic success by both traditional and untraditional metrics: 484 presentations were made by 443 attendees, who collectively consumed approximately 90 liters of wine and 2000 bottles of beer over the course of the week. At the closing ceremony, participants were able to reflect on the week and get excite...d about the next two IPA conferences, SouthCOP in New Zealand in December 2019 and ICOP 2020 in Lanzhou, China. PYRN Executive Committee members Helena Bergstedt and Jannik Martens presented the PYRN presentation awards to Samuel Gagnon and Constanza Morino for having the best oral and poster presentation, respectively. The IPA extends thanks to all involved for the invigorating and inspiring week! See More+2International Permafrost Association added 4 new photos.June 28, 2018 \u00b7 The past days at EUCOP5 have been packed with both indoor and outdoor scientific activity! Monday, Tuesday, and Thursday were filled with presentations during four main oral presentation sessions per day and an afternoon poster session every afternoon. Wednesday was the first of two local excursion days, with participants going to the D\u00e9rochoir rock glacier or Br\u00e9vent-Montenvers/Mer de Glace. Participants have also enjoyed networking and relaxing with colleagues during coffee breaks, lunches, and at the PYRN tartiflette evening.International Permafrost Association added 2 new photos.June 25, 2018 \u00b7 Official opening of EUCOP5 and 2018 Lifetime Achievement Award presented to Wilfried Haeberli The 5th European Conference on Permafrost officially began this morning at the Opening Ceremony at Le Majestic Congress in Chamonix. Participants were welcomed by Philip Deline on behalf of the Local Organizing Committee, the mayor of Chamonix, and IPA President Hanne Christiansen. During the ceremony, the 2018 Lifetime Achievement Award was presented to Wilfried Haeberli, a prolific... permafrost scientist and general cryosphere expert with extensive experience studying and working in the Alps. The IPA was pleased to have such a fitting occasion to honor Prof. Dr. Haeberli. The ceremony also included an overview of EUCOP5 PYRN activities by outgoing PYRN Vice-President Justine Ramage, and closing remarks by Philip Deline. Everyone is looking forward to the rest of the week! See MoreInternational Permafrost Association added 2 new photos.June 24, 2018 \u00b7 27th IPA Council Meeting held in Chamonix The Council of the International Permafrost Association convened in Chamonix, France on 24 June as part of the 5th European Conference on Permafrost (EUCOP5), an IPA regional conference. Council members reviewed the IPA\u2019s activities over the past two years (when the Council last met), and had a number of discussions related to our Regional and International Conferences on Permafrost, which are a priority of the IPA. The IPA was pleased to gather today as the governing body of the association and looks forward to the official opening of EUCOP5 tomorrow. Follow along with the upcoming week's news on our website (https://ipa.arcticportal.org/news) and here on Facebook.See More", "2015 09 17 Perg\u00e9lisol : Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Bouchard : Free Download, Borrow, and Streaming : Internet Archive Skip to main content Search the history of over 349 billion web pages on the Internet. search Search the Wayback Machine Featured texts All Texts latest This Just In Smithsonian Libraries FEDLINK (US) Genealogy Lincoln Collection Additional Collections Books to Borrow Top American Libraries Canadian Libraries Universal Library Community Texts Project Gutenberg Biodiversity Heritage Library Children's Library Open Library Books by Language Featured movies All Video latest This Just In Prelinger Archives Democracy Now! Occupy Wall Street TV NSA Clip Library TV News Top Animation & Cartoons Arts & Music Community Video Computers & Technology Cultural & Academic Films Ephemeral Films Movies Understanding 9/11 News & Public Affairs Spirituality & Religion Sports Videos Television Videogame Videos Vlogs Youth Media Featured audio All Audio latest This Just In Grateful Dead Netlabels Old Time Radio 78 RPMs and Cylinder Recordings Live Music Archive Top Audio Books & Poetry Co