r The Win daily email newsletter for the top stories every day. An error has occured Please re-enter your email address. Thanks for signing up! You'll now receive the top For The Win stories each day directly in your inbox. Close \u00d7 NFL NBA NCAAB MMA WWE MLB Soccer NCAAF Golf Fan Index Pro Football Fan Index College Football Fan Index Racing Tennis NHL Boxing NASCAR Culture Olympics Lists Longform Outdoors 10 best snow games in sports history 10 best snow games in sports history Sports 10 best snow games in sports history By Nate Scott February 20, 2019 7:44 am Follow\t\t\t\t\t@aNateScott shares share tweet pin sms send email By:\t\tNate Scott | February 20, 2019 7:44 am Follow @aNateScott A massive snow storm is battering the eastern seaboard of the United States today, and with tons of people stuck home from work and school, we thought we\u2019d take a moment to look back at some of the best snow moments in sports history. Sports are more fun when the weather is a mess, and these games capture that. For the purposes of this list, we are excluding sports that are played on snow and ice, so snowboarding, skiing, moguls, bobsledding, figure skating, and hockey are all out. Sorry, gang. I don\u2019t make up the rules of our fake internet lists. (I totally make up the rules of our fake internet lists.) Let\u2019s get to the 10 best snow games in sports history. 10. Bills vs. Browns 2007 Photo by Scott Boehm/Getty Images This game will always stick out as a perfect snow football game because of just how miserable it was. The Browns won 8-0, the game had to be stopped multiple times to shovel the lines on the field, and every single fan in attendance looked miserable. Perfect. 9. Orioles Opening Day 2003 (AP Photo/Nick Wass) The combination of the excitement and pageantry of Opening Day combined with the backdrop of gently falling snow made the Orioles\u2019 game against the Indians an instant Camden Yards classic. Plus it gave us this iconic play: 8. 2000 Independence Bowl A freak snowstorm in Louisiana for a bowl game between Texas A&M and Mississippi State is as wonderful as you think it is. Even better? The Bulldogs won 43-41 in an overtime thriller. 7. The 1979 Cotton Bowl (AP Photo/WFH) Notre Dame, helmed by Joe Montana, took on the University of Houston in an absolutely frigid Cotton Bowl played in 1979. The game earned the moniker The Chicken Soup Game, as it was played during the worst ice storm in Dallas in years. The match was more than just bad weather, though, as Montana led the Fighting Irish to an exciting 35-34 win. 6. The 2014 Winter Classic Julian H. Gonzalez /Detroit Free Press Ok in the intro we said no ice hockey, but I\u2019m making an exception for the 2014 Winter Classic, which gave us the glorious site of ice hockey being played on HD television with fat snowflakes falling on the Big House in Michigan. 5. The Leon Lett Game Poor Leon Lett. His Thanksgiving day blunder against the Miami Dolphins gave the Cowboys one of the more iconic losses of the franchise\u2019s history. 4. U.S. beats Costa Rica in a snow storm Qualifying for the World Cup is something no American soccer fan takes for granted anymore. This match helped them do so in the run up to the 2014 World Cup, and what a match it was \u2013 played in a snowstorm in Denver, and resulting in a 1-0 USMNT win. 3. 1967 NFL Championship: The Ice Bowl (AP Photo) The 1967 NFL Championship Game was more ice than snow, but we\u2019re going to include it here because those guys looked pretty cold and we\u2019ll give them the benefit of the doubt. The Green Bay Packers played the Dallas Cowboys at Lambeau Field in sub-zero temperatures, with the Packers winning 21-17 and claiming The Ice Bowl. 2. Michigan vs. Ohio State 1950 We move from The Ice Bowl to The Snow Bowl. The game between Michigan and Ohio State in a driving snow storm ended with Michigan winning 9-3 and claiming the Big Ten Championship, and a spot in the Rose Bowl. 1. The Tuck Rule / Vinatieri game AP Photo/Elise Amendola How else could it end? The 2001 AFC Divisional Playoff Game gave us the introduction of the \u201ctuck rule\u201d into the lexicon of even casual sports fans, the first iconic Adam Vinatieri game-winning kick, and the launch of the Patriots NFL dynasty. If this game goes differently, who knows if the Patriots even become who they become? Gallery The lamest nicknames in sports, from 'Mr. Big Chest' to 'The Claw' view 11 images Lists, snow, Sports shares share tweet pin sms send email Nate Scott Follow @aNateScott Nate Scott is the managing editor of FTW. More \u2026 Recommended Videos More FTW 51m ago Soccer Sergio Ramos' intentional suspension backfires for Real Madrid vs. Ajax 1.3k shares10hr ago NBA NBA fans can't stop piling on LeBron, who's 2-5 after activating 'playoff mode' early 1hr ago Soccer See all the goals from Ajax's stunning 4-1 win over Real Madrid From The Web The Latest 31m NCAAB 31m ago Watch Champ Week College Basketball Tonight Live on ESPN+ March 5, 2019 5:30 pm \u00b7 FTW Staff Watch Champ Week with ESPN+ on the road to the Tournament. 47m NFL 47m ago What Lincoln Riley had to say about Kyler Murray's leadership ability March 5, 2019 5:14 pm \u00b7 Andrew Joseph Kyler Murray\u2019s leadership came into question at the combine. 51m Soccer 51m ago Sergio Ramos' intentional suspension backfires for Real Madrid vs. Ajax March 5, 2019 5:09 pm \u00b7 Nate Scott Real Madrid\u2019s Sergio Ramos made the tactical decision to get a yellow card in the first leg against Ajax. That backfired (\u2026) 1hr Soccer 1hr ago USA vs. Brazil: Match Preview, How to Watch USWNT Online, SheBelieves Cup Live Stream, Start Time, TV Channel March 5, 2019 5:00 pm \u00b7 FTW Staff USA vs. Brazil: Match Preview, How to Watch USWNT Online 1hr NBA 1hr ago Houston Rockets vs Toronto Raptors: Game Preview, Live Stream, Start Time, TV Channel, How to Watch NBA Online March 5, 2019 5:00 pm \u00b7 FTW Staff Raptors vs. Rockets Stream 1hr Soccer 1hr a