 10/10 Special Chests found in Bitterfrost Frontier 1 15/15 Special Chests found in Bitterfrost Frontier 1 19/19 Special Chests found in Bitterfrost Frontier 3 Vigilant 5 Get all the wounded Vigil to safety without having to revive any of them Reward: 2 Frozen Exotic Weapon Fragment Saved All the Vigil 5 Cultural Attach\u00e9 5 Bring Aurene souvenirs from around Tyria to teach her about the cultures of the world. Collected 7/7 Souvenirs 5 Notes[edit] Anomaly: Delicious Desserts are not acquired in the bitter cold despite the achievements description, you get them at the heart in the southeast. Bug: Heart, Moxie, and Many Sweaters does not require the player to be alive when they have 20 stacks of Bitter Cold. Bitter Cold accumulates even when defeated, so simply being in a Bitter Cold area long enough will grant the achievement. There are several Diving Goggles placed around the Bitter Cold area. All of them are placed above solid ice. For Dive Master: Cold Feet to be successful, you must use the highest one, in the southeastern corner of the area. This one will allow you to safely break through the ice to the water below; aim for the obvious patch of ice. There is also an Icebound Chest in the water below the dive point. Using any of the other dive points will result in the ice not breaking and you taking falling damage. Several collections components can can be bought and sold on the Trading Post. The Gift of Aurene collection - Each part can only be crafted once per day per account, on the standard daily reset. The parts are tradable, but the complete doll is account-bound. The Koda's Blessing collection - Both the Offering Basket and complete Offering to Koda items are tradable. Trivia[edit] The \"Playing Chicken\" achievement is likely a reference to The Legend of Zelda series, in which the protagonist struggles with aggressive chickens. Achievements Daily Daily Daily Lunar New Year Daily Fractals Daily Thunderhead Peaks Daily Jahai Bluffs Daily Domain of Kourn