dingen, the full, illustrated, multi-language version of the glossary is available at: http://nsidc.org/fgdc/glossary The references and English definitions are available in HTML and PDF formats. The introduction, illustrations, and multi-language terms are available in PDF format. Please contact NSIDC User Services with any questions: CIRES, 449 UCB University of Colorado Boulder, CO 80309-0449 USA Phone: 303-492-6199 Fax: 303-492-2468 E-mail: nsidc@nsidc.org URL: http://nsidc.org ArcticInfo About Submission Subscribe Past Announcement Search Arctic Research Consortium of the United States 3535 College Road Suite 101 Fairbanks, Alaska 99709-3710 907-474-1600 info@arcus.org ARCUS is a nonprofit organization consisting of institutions organized and operated for educational, professional, or scientific purposes to advance arctic research and education. This website is supported in part by the National Science Foundation under Cooperative Agreement No. PLR-1304316. Any opinions, findings, and conclusions or recommendations expressed in this material are those of the author(s) and do not necessarily reflect the views of the National Science Foundation. AboutValues, Vision, and Mission Staff Board of Directors Advisory Council Services Contact ARCUS Logo Employment Opportunities Donate Privacy Policy MembershipMember Information ARCUS Members Member Representatives Organizational Member Application Annual Meetings ProgramsStudy of Environmental Arctic Change Sea Ice Prediction Network Sea Ice Outlook Sea Ice for Walrus Outlook Indigenous Scholars External Collaborations for the Interagency Arctic Research Policy Committee PolarTREC The Arctic in the Classroom Logistics Arctic System Science Program Bering Ecosystem Science Joint Science Education Project (JSEP) MeetingsARCUS at POLAR2018 Women's Perspectives Luncheon at Polar2018 Research Seminar Series Alaska Marine Science Symposium 2018 AGU Community Meetings ARCUS Annual Meetings Arctic Research Day Arctic Science Su